Job_Desc:
At Star, we connect strategy, insights, design, and engineering into a seamless workflow devised to support our clients every step of the way—no matter how long or complex their journey. We anchor everything we do in clear and compelling endgames, which in turn enable our multidisciplinary teams to create superior solutions and impressive commercial returns for our clients.
Star is truly global. That is why we are the first major consulting company that does not have headquarters. Instead, we have many front doors, spanning Silicon Valley, Tokyo, London, Munich, Copenhagen, Kyiv, Wroclaw, Ho Chi Minh City, and other vibrant design, technology, and creative nuclei of the world. Our spirited and growing 1000+ strong Star Crew takes great pride in working side by side with their trailblazing counterparts at some of the world’s most disruptive “unicorn” startups and iconic global brands like Lufthansa, Dolby Laboratories, BMW, Panasonic, Walmart, and Zeiss.
Our mission is to make every great person, every great idea, and every great company shine. That’s why we’re called Star.
The Opportunity
Star is looking to hire a Corporate Strategy Manager who will define, lead and execute a wide variety of strategic programs and initiatives. It’s a unique opportunity to impact the growth and evolution of a fast-growing consultancy. You will be working closely with our VP of Corporate Strategy, the Chairman and the Executive Leadership team to identify strategic needs and opportunities and drive our efforts to guide Star in the right strategic direction.
In addition to impacting Star’s future, you will also be expected to play a critical role in shaping how our corporate strategy group operates and evolves. We have an ambitious endgame for Star, and you will be central to making it a reality. As Star grows, you will grow and rise as well.
We’d love to hear from you if the following describes you:
Embodies a global mindset, thrives while working with internal and external stakeholders from various locations, professions and backgrounds;
Naturally curious, able to take on a steep learning curve and understand new domains or challenges;
Challenges a ‘business-as-usual’ attitude, doesn’t settle for the status quo and always pushes people around you, and the company at large, to be better;
Possesses a high EQ and business intuition;
Works well independently, takes initiative and is able to execute on tasks with concise guidance and input;
Thrives within ambiguity and adapts to changing circumstances.
You
Qualifications and experience:
5+ years of professional experience, including 2+ years of management consulting, corporate strategy, or similar experience;
Strong project management skills, able to oversee and contribute to multiple parallel initiatives;
Excellent presentation skills, able to clearly communicate compelling messages to senior internal and external audiences;
Effective communication skills, able to engage with stakeholders from a variety of functions and seniority levels;
Strong end-to-end research and analysis skills - rigorous data collection, deep analysis, clear insights and pragmatic recommendations;
Fluent written and spoken English skills.
Would be a plus:
Strong understanding of consultancy industry and business models;
Capable of modeling future scenarios using a blend of financial, operational and market data;
Experience hiring, developing, inspiring and managing junior team members;
M&A experience as advisor, consultant or in-house stakeholder;
Capable of planning and facilitating strategy workshops and similar events.
Experience with joint ventures, strategic alliances, etc.;
Experience with creating thought leadership content;
Other language proficiencies.
﻿
Responsibilities
As a leading member of our Corporate Strategy team, you will be directly responsible for shaping Star’s future across business units and functions. Your ability to cooperate with our leaders will have a tangible impact on the future success of Star.
Lead the definition and execution of strategy programs and initiatives;
Shape the agenda for your work, building on your own insights, best practices and learning from working with strategy and industry leaders;
Support business units and functions with strategic planning and ensure all parts of the company are working towards the same end goal as Star;
Drive efforts to ensure Star is well-positioned for its potential future scenarios (going public, staying private, being acquired);
Be an internal champion of end goal thinking, and evangelize our own end goal and the strategy for getting to it;
Build and maintain a strong understanding of industry trends and the competitive landscape, and use that knowledge to inform strategy programs, M&A strategy, and strategic planning;
Partner with M&A groups on select transactions with market analysis, target company assessment, business case development, and due diligence;
Facilitate the annual strategy & planning cycle.
Compensations and Benefits
We offer a rewarding compensation and benefits package, intellectually and creatively stimulating environment, professional flexibility and unique international travel opportunities.
Star is an Equal Opportunity Employer. We believe that equity, diversity and inclusion are key to our ability to provide our clients and crew members with unique business and career outcomes. Your race, color, ancestry, religion, gender, identity, sexual orientation, age, marital status, disability have no effect on our hiring decisions. If you have a special need that requires accommodation, please let us know.
